    <bioghist>Captain, later colonel in the 8th Michigan Cavalry during the Civil War.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Letters to family describing activities and events while serving in the Civil War (original letters and typescripts); speeches given after the war; personal and service-related documents. There are also scattered letters of family members, Frank W. Mix, serving with the 4th Michigan Cavalry; Edward H. Mix, serving with the 4th Connecticut Infantry; and Amelia Mix, wife of Elisha Mix. Also correspondence (1848-1849) from William G. Butler describing conditions in Saugatuck, Mich.</scopecontent>
